<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>BCP Non-Disclosure Agreement</title>
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Libre+Baskerville:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Montserrat:ital,wght@0,100..900;1,100..900&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Poppins"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <style>
      body {
        font-size: 11pt;
        color: #000;
        padding-top: 40px;
        line-height: 1.2;
        font-family: "Aptos", "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif;
        padding: 10px;
        max-width: 100%;
        background-color: #fff;
        text-align: justify;
      }
      h1 {
        text-align: center;
      }
      h2 {
        text-align: center;
        font-weight: bold;
        color: #0f4761;
        text-align: justify;
      }
      h3 {
        color: #801423;
        font-weight: bold;
        text-align: justify;
      }
      h4 {
        text-align: justify;
      }
      p {
        /* margin-bottom: 1em; */
        margin-top: -10px;
        text-align: justify;
      }
      li {
        text-align: justify;
        margin-bottom: 2px;
      }
      ul {
        margin-top: -10px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT</h1>
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: -20px">
      (For Manuscript Submission and Review)
    </p>

    <p>
      This <strong>Non-Disclosure Agreement (the “Agreement”)</strong> is
      entered into as of <strong><%= date %></strong>, by and between:
    </p>
    <p style="padding-top: 5px;">
      <strong>BookCraft Publishers LLC</strong>, a company registered under the
      laws of Texas, USA, with its principal office at
      <strong>
        12828 Willow Centre Dr Ste D # 225 Houston TX, USA 77066,</strong
      >
      Phone: <strong>888 905 0868,</strong> and Email:
      <strong>info@bookcraftpublishers.com</strong> (hereinafter individually
      referred to as the “Recipient” or “BookCraft Publishers”)
    </p>
    <p style="padding-top: 5px; ">and</p>

    <p style="padding-top: 5px;">
      <strong><%= authorTitle %> <%= authorFullName %></strong>, Phone:
      <strong><%= authorPhone %></strong>, and Email:
      <strong><%= authorEmail %></strong> (hereinafter individually referred to
      as the “Disclosing Party” or "Author").
    </p>

    <p style="padding-top: 5px;">
      (Each may individually be referred to as a <strong>"Party"</strong> and
      collectively as the <strong>"Parties"</strong>).
    </p>

    <h3>1. Purpose of the Agreement</h3>
    <p>
      The <strong>Author</strong> wishes to submit a manuscript (the
      “Confidential Information”) to <strong>BookCraft Publishers</strong> for
      <strong>evaluation and review</strong> to determine the feasibility of
      <strong>publishing, editing, or other related services.</strong> To
      protect the confidentiality of the manuscript, the Parties agree to the
      terms outlined below.
    </p>

    <h3>2. Definition of Confidential Information</h3>
    <p>
      For the purposes of this Agreement, "Confidential Information" includes,
      but is not limited to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        The manuscript or any portion thereof (whether written, digital, or
        oral).
      </li>
      <li>
        Any related notes, summaries, outlines, drafts, synopses, or concepts.
      </li>
      <li>
        Any discussions, feedback, or evaluations of the manuscript provided by
        <strong>BookCraft Publishers</strong>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Any proprietary information, ideas, plotlines, characters, research, and
        other creative materials disclosed by the <strong>Author</strong>.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Obligations of Confidentiality</h3>
    <p>The <strong>Recipient</strong> agrees:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Not to disclose, share, copy, reproduce, or distribute</strong>
        any part of the Confidential Information to third parties without the
        <strong>Author's</strong> prior written consent.
      </li>
      <li>
        To use the Confidential Information
        <strong>solely to evaluate</strong> the manuscript for potential
        <strong>publishing, editing, or related services.</strong>
      </li>
      <li>
        To take <strong>reasonable precautions</strong> to safeguard the
        Confidential Information from unauthorized disclosure.
      </li>
      <li>
        To <strong>return or destroy</strong> all Confidential Information upon
        the Author’s request if no publishing or service agreement is signed.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h3>4. Exceptions to Confidentiality</h3>
    <p>
      The obligations of confidentiality shall not apply to information that:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Was <strong>already in the public domain</strong> at the time of
        disclosure.
      </li>
      <li>
        Becomes publicly available <strong>without breach</strong> of this
        Agreement.
      </li>
      <li>
        Was independently developed by the <strong>Recipient</strong> without
        reference to the Confidential Information.
      </li>
      <li>
        Is required to be disclosed by
        <strong>law, regulation, or court order,</strong> provided that the
        <strong>Recipient</strong> notifies the <strong>Author</strong> in
        advance.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. No Rights or License</h3>
    <p>
      This Agreement <strong>does not grant</strong> the
      <strong>Recipient</strong> any ownership or rights to the
      <strong>Author’s</strong> manuscript, copyrights, trademarks, or
      intellectual property.
    </p>
    <p>
      The <strong>Author</strong> retains
      <strong>all intellectual property rights</strong> in the manuscript.
      <strong>BookCraft Publishers</strong> agrees
      <strong>not to claim ownership</strong> of any portion of the manuscript
      unless a <strong>separate publishing or service agreement</strong> is
      executed between the Parties.
    </p>

    <h3>6. No Obligation to Publish</h3>
    <p>This Agreement does not:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong> Obligate</strong> the <strong>Recipient</strong> to publish,
        promote, or engage in any further work on the manuscript.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Guarantee</strong> the Author any publishing agreement or
        service contract.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Both Parties agree that any future collaboration will be
      <strong>subject to a separate agreement.</strong>
    </p>

    <h3>7. Term and Termination</h3>

    <ul>
      <li>
        This Agreement remains in effect<strong> for three (3) years</strong>
        from the Effective Date.
      </li>
      <li>
        Either Party may terminate this Agreement with
        <strong>written notice,</strong> but the confidentiality obligations
        shall survive for a period of <strong>three (3) years</strong> after
        termination.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>8. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution</h3>
    <p>
      This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the
      <strong>laws of Texas, USA.</strong> Any disputes arising under this
      Agreement shall be resolved through
      <strong>good-faith negotiations.</strong> If unresolved, disputes shall be
      settled through<strong>
        binding arbitration in Houston, Texas, USA.</strong
      >
    </p>

    <h3>9. Miscellaneous</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>No Waiver: </strong>  Failure to enforce any provision does not
        constitute a waiver.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>No Transfer of Rights: </strong>  Neither Party may assign this
        Agreement without prior written consent.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Entire Agreement: </strong>  This Agreement represents the
        <strong>entire understanding</strong> between the Parties regarding
        confidentiality.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>10. Signature and Acknowledgment</h3>
    <p>
      By signing below, both Parties agree to be bound by the terms of this
      Agreement.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong style="color: #0f4761; font-size: 16px">
        BookCraft Publishers
      </strong>
      <br />
      Authorized Representative: <%= signature %><br />
      Signature: <% if (signature === "Jerry Miller") { %>
      <img
        src="https://www.bookcraftpublishers.com/cdn-cgi/imagedelivery/tXX1eXFTW8RWMWWjsrsa2A/095b9d95-8c48-42a2-8128-de189ce75f00/Desktop960"
        alt="Jerry Miller Signature"
        style="width: 20%; display: block; margin-top: 4px"
      />
      <% } else if (signature === "Robert Williams") { %>
      <img
        src="https://www.bookcraftpublishers.com/cdn-cgi/imagedelivery/tXX1eXFTW8RWMWWjsrsa2A/5a1fc027-4bed-4722-f7ab-420033007f00/Desktop960"
        alt="Robert Williams Signature"
        style="width: 20%; display: block; margin-top: 4px"
      />
      <% } else { %> _______________________ <% } %>
      <br />
      Date: _______________________
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong style="color: #0f4761; font-size: 16px">Author</strong><br />
      Full Name: _______________________<br />
      Signature: _______________________<br />
      Date: _______________________
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
